cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use AEDIN's data, claims, methodology, or software in your
  research, please cite it as below.
title: >-
  AEDIN: An open agroecological knowledge base with multi-critic
  AI consensus verification
abstract: >-
  AEDIN extracts atomic agroecological claims — pest, pathogen,
  beneficial-insect, pollinator, mycorrhizal, soil, and crop-trait
  relationships — from open-access scientific literature using a
  large-language-model extraction pipeline, then verifies each claim
  through a multi-critic AI consensus gate: two independent specialty
  critics (agroecologist plus a domain expert from entomology, plant
  pathology, soil science, or horticulture) must agree on plausibility,
  with no implausible verdict, before a claim is promoted to public
  visibility. Verified claims are published with verbatim source quotes,
  page citations, and the full multi-critic verdict trail. Vocabulary is
  aligned with the Global Biotic Interactions (GloBI) Relations Ontology
  so claims can be pushed back to the public GloBI corpus.
